        "title": "How do I install a certificate in the trusted certificates keystore within WebSphere?",
        "body": "<p>Our network guy provided us a .cer file in order to install on our laptop running Windows XP with Eclipse and WebSphere. I have seen the following posts: <\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6431383/using-spring-ldap-with-ssl\">using spring-ldap with ssl<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>However I am unsure as to where/how to install the .cer file. <\/p>\n\n<p>I have also seen the following post:<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/373295/digital-certificate-how-to-import-cer-file-in-to-truststore-file-using\">Digital Certificate: How to import .cer file in to .truststore file using?<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Again I just don't know what the keystore is. Is it cacerts?<\/p>\n\n<p>Any help will be highly appreciated. <\/p>\n",
